14 §2502. Limitation of liability for flood mitigation preparations
15 A.(1) Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no
16 political subdivision created pursuant to this Chapter and authorized to
17 establish, construct, operate, and maintain freshwater systems, nor any officer,
18 employee, or agent thereof, shall be liable for any damage caused by or resulting
19 from any act or omission in reducing or ceasing pumping operations or
20 operating water control structures for the purpose of lowering water levels
21 pursuant to an operational plan implemented in preparation for a weather
22 event forecasted by the National Weather Service or the Governor's Office of
23 Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness.
24 (2) The limitation of liability provided in this Section shall not apply to
25 acts or omissions constituting gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct.
26 B. The provisions of this Section shall apply only to a political
27 subdivision whose territorial jurisdiction encompasses four parishes, at least
